  "text": "In Table 3 , the correlation coefficients of S grd , S geod , T grd , and T geod with the set of indices AE, AL, AU, and PCI are also fairly strong, in the range 0.583-0.710, with AU being the poorest. These four indices are measures of the strengths of high-latitude currents (with AE algebraically defined as AE = AU À AL). The correlation of S grd , S geod , T grd , and T geod with Dst* is also fairly strong in Table 3 . Dst* is a measure of the plasma diamagnetism in the inner magnetosphere [Dessler and Parker, 1959] , produced by ions with orbits trapped in the dipolar magnetosphere [CITATION_1] and by plasma flowing past the dipole from the nightside to the dayside [CITATION_2] . Note in Table 3 that the correlations of the ULF indices with the pressure-corrected index Dst* are significantly higher than with the uncorrected Dst index. Here the formula Dst* = Dst À 20.7P ram + 27.7 [CITATION_3] ] is used to produce Dst* from Dst, where the solar wind ram pressure P ram = m p nv sw 2 is in units of nPa.",
